Thickness Gauge Sensor using two ultrasonic sensors desinged for thin material.

This follows ASTM  E797 "Standard Practice for Measuring Thickness by Manual Ultrasonic Pulse-Echo Contact Method"

Background 
```
d_ultrasonic = v_sound*t/2
```
where 
  - v_sound is the speed of sound
  - t is the recorded duration of the pulse from transmitter to reciever of an ultrasonic sensor

Placing sensors apart at a known reference distance, d_reference, we can determine the thickness by doing 
```
  d_thickness = d_reference - (d_ultrasonic_1 + d_ultrasonic_2)
```

If ultrasonic sensor is greater than 10Hz, than we can have a wavelength of 
```
lambda  = v_sound / frequency 
        = (343 m/s) / (10 Mhz)
        = 34.3 micrometers
```

Thus we can measuere small micrometer distance to a precision of 34.3 micrometers. for 100 MHz we can get 3.43 micrometer resolution. 

The code in this repository is a simple proof of concept using arduino libraries. 